1. Install Django (GeoDjango included)
	- Django weirdness with PostGIS. Use https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/16778.
    - Update PYTHONPATH so Python can find modules.
    - Remember to change settings.py. Namely the DATABASES and INSTALLED_APPS settings.

2. Install PostgreSQL
	- Needs psycopg2 to work properly with Python.
    - Initialize database cluster. Optionally set PG_DATA environment variable if you don't
    	want to specify cluster location every time.

3. Install PostGIS
    - MUST do a psql -f on postgis.sql and spatial_ref_sys.sql.
    - Make sure you create a template_postgis database for testing.
    
#!/bin/sh
POST_GIS_DIR="/usr/local/Cellar/postgis/1.5.3/share/postgis"

brew install postgresql
brew install postgis
brew install gdal

pip install django
pip install psycopg2   	

initdb /usr/local/var/postgres

createdb gisdb
createdb template_postgis

psql -d gisdb -f $POST_GIS_DIR/postgis.sql
psql -d gisdb -f $POST_GIS_DIR/spatial_ref_sys.sql
psql -d template_postgis -f $POST_GIS_DIR/postgis.sql
psql -d template_postgis -f $POST_GIS_DIR/spatial_ref_sys.sql

pg_ctl -l /usr/local/var/postgres/server.log start
    
